[Student "S"]
{NORTH has a balanced 23-point hand. He opens 2\C.

With 6 points and two 4-card Majors, SOUTH can only say 2\D.

NORTH shows his minimum hand with a 2NT rebid.

Now SOUTH bids 3\C. This is not the second negative, but rather it is Stayman.

When NORTH shows his \S suit SOUTH bids 4\S.}

